column33: Maritza had a bit of a fall, but she was okay. Anne also fell and hurt her leg. We put a bandage on it and she finished the ride. Anne has a problem with when she starts to rides to the left into the opposite lane and that should be worked on with her. It could be very dangerous if a car were to ever be coming. Other than that I was really proud of everyone for keeping a positive attitude and pushing through the ride. I was sweep and it was awesome seeing everyone push themselves.

Ride was great. On the way back, I couldn't pedal for a moment (something with the gears) and the fall broke a metal piece on my back tire. Sam drove me back. J&A fixed it up, so bike is all good!
